  "intermediate_belief": "If I can't decide on a clear direction for my life, it means I'm not competent enough to handle important decisions. I need to be certain about my future to feel secure and successful. If I make the wrong choice, it will reflect poorly on my abilities.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I keep feeling lost about my life direction, it means I'll never figure things out and nothing I do will matter. My past achievements won't count if I can't move forward.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client uses structured strategies and reminders to manage daily tasks and reduce anxiety. When faced with major decisions, they may avoid making choices, ruminate about options, or seek temporary distractions to escape the discomfort of uncertainty.",
